Which version of `photutils` are you trying to install?  If you are installing the latest *released* version (0.2.2), you do not need `Cython` and `pip install photutils` should work fine. A recommended alternative is to use `conda install photutils -c astropy`.

If you are trying to install a *development* version, then you need `Cython`, a C compiler suite (e.g. XCode for OSX), and the development headers for `Python` and `Numpy`.  Please see http://photutils.readthedocs.io/en/latest/photutils/install.html#installing-the-latest-development-version.

