I'm glad you worked on this bug, but I don't think you completely understood the issue.

"You want to change base icon size one for good, am I right?"
No, that is not what we're doing.  We don't want to set a base font size in FontAwesome for our entire project, we want to specify a font size for individual icons on a case-by-case basis.  As an example, here's what we're doing, which has worked for many previous versions of FontAwesome:

HTML:
<button class="select" onclick="...">
    <i class="fa fa-icon-glass"></i>
</button>

CSS:
button {
    &.select {
        > i {
            &.fa-icon-glass {
                &:before {
                    font-size: 18px;
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

With the addition of the following line in v4.2, the custom font size specification no longer works:

.fa {
    font: normal normal normal 14px/1 FontAwesome; // shortening font declaration
    font-size: inherit; // can't have font-size inherit on line above, so need to override
}

The reason that this causes problems is, that since you included the font size inside a single-line "font" command, you have to issue a new "font" command in order to override it, which means that we have to inspect thousands of lines of SASS code and change all of our "font-size" commands to "font" commands, which is very time consuming, and highly redundant (since FontAwesome needs to be specified over and over).  I suggest changing it back to the v4.1 version, which has the same effect of setting FontAwesome as the default font without hard-coding a font size into the "font" command:

.fa {
font-family: FontAwesome;
// ** delete the font-size: inherit command, it's unnecessary
}

Does that explain our issue better?

