@predatell I agree with you, it's very convenient to be able to let `pip` figure out the versions that "work" when you put all the software together.

My issue is with the word "work" and what that means.  We only know if software works if it was tested!  

And I am not arguing for pinning a single version: I am arguing for pinning all versions that the developer knows works with their software product and are tested in CI.  If they are not in CI, or untested yet, then upstream should not add them.

@bacongobbler nice work so far!  The developer UX seems like what we want.  The cron implementation is clever.  My big concern at the moment is how we handle cert chains -- which are quite common.  To make sure we're covered, let's add a test case for them in the unit tests.

With regard to wildcard domains, I agree we can tackle that later if needed.  My guess is most folks will want to put a wildcard cert on the router to handle SSL for _all_ their apps, as you proposed.  This PR is really about custom SSL for specific apps, which will often have a custom domain.

I look forward to testing this!

