@cpcloud Digging in, looks like on `odo` master in [`odo.backends.sql.py`](https://github.com/blaze/odo/blob/master/odo/backends/sql.py#L23) there is a `from datashape import Map`.  `Map` is a new addition to `datashape`, so this triggers an `ImportError` in `odo`, which is silently swallowed by Blaze, as you suspected.

The net effect is that none of the SQL odo backends are registered, and the `impala` connection fails.

Updating `datashape` provides `datashape.Map`, odo's import is happy, and `impala` URIs are registered.

